> the road. 
>     A few weeks later, we noticed that that bus
> never moved.  We stopped and 
> talked to the owner, and he said he went "down
> south" to get a clean rust 
> free bus, so he would have something solid to work
> with.  Shortly after he 
> trailered it up here (Wisconsin), the motor quit
> running, so there the bus 
> sat. 
>     Fast forward to a few months ago.   Bus is STILL
> sitting in the same 
> spot, outside, and when I stopped by to inquire
> about the bus, the owner had 
> the same attitude as the previous story....."Does it
> SAY for sale on it?!? I 
> am sooo sick of you (----) people stopping
> here....."  and on and on.
> 
>        I did manage to sneak a peak at that bus
> before I was tossed off the 
> property.   What was once a gorgeous bus, is going
> downhill fast.  Sitting 
> outside after 4 years on a farm, through 4 wisconsin
> winters, and, to make 
> matters worse, all of the runoff from the roof of
> the barn lands directly on 
> the bus...you can only imagine.
> 
>    What prompts some people to do this, to what was
> once a great bus?
